President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to appoint Tyler Beck Goodspeed of New Hampshire as a Member of the Council of Economic Advisers. Goodspeed currently serves as the Chief Economist for Macroeconomic Policy on the Council of Economic Advisers. He has previously worked as a lecturer in economics at King's College London and on the faculty of economics at the University of Oxford. Goodspeed has published extensively on the economic history of money and banking, focusing on the role of access to credit in mitigating adverse aggregate shocks and the use of extended and contingent liability in banking. He holds degrees from Harvard University and the University of Cambridge.